title: Grateful Dead Live at Great Western LA Forum on 1989-02-11
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step, Minglewood Blues, Candyman, Big River, Built To Last, Queen Jane Approximately, We Can Run But We Can't Hide, Bird Song

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Women Are Smarter, Standing On the Moon, Estimated Prophet-> Jam-> I Will Take You Home-> Drums*-> Eyes Of The World-> I Need A Miracle-> Black Peter-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Box Of Rain

*with Airto Moreira, Flora Purim and Diana Moreira

reviews.review_text: Bassy, muffled, unbalanced SBD As far as I can tell, a nice-sounding but unremarkable show.
need good  bass speakers  one of best  box of rain  you ever hear

Good show, good sound Ok: After a solid set one, set two really takes off.  The Estimated gets real spacy before dropping into Take you Home; very cool.  The drums with Flora and Airto is awesome.  Eyes out of that is great.  Nice Black Peter too.  1989 Dead was off to a good start.  The 2/10 show is also real good, with a trippy extended playing in the Band.  The 2/5/89 Show in Oakland also has a Nice PITB.
